##Conditioning of BV in LowCF

conditioningexp = read.csv(file = "LowCF_Conditioning/conditioning_combined.csv")
onlyevolution= subset(conditioningexp, Staus %in% "1")
summary_data_condition2 <- onlyevolution %>%
  group_by(Media, Strain, Day) %>%
  summarise(mean_value = mean(log),
            sd_value = sd(log),
            count = n())
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Media', 'Strain'. You can override using
## the `.groups` argument.
conditioning_plot=ggplot(data = summary_data_condition2, aes(x = Day, y = mean_value,)) + 
  geom_line(color = "#7bccc4", size = 1.2) + 
  geom_point(data = onlyevolution, aes(x = Day, y = log)) + 
  geom_errorbar(data = summary_data_condition2, aes(x = Day, ymin = mean_value - sd_value, ymax = mean_value + sd_value), width = 0.5) + 
  ylim(0, 10) + 
  geom_vline(xintercept = c(5, 10), color = "black", linetype = "dotted", size = 0.8) + 
  annotate("text", x = 2.5, y = 2.5, label = "25% LowCF", size = 5) +  
  annotate("text", x = 7.5, y = 2.5, label = "50% LowCF", size = 5) +   
  annotate("text", x = 12.5, y = 2.5, label = "100% LowCF", size = 5) +  
  theme(legend.position = "right") + 
  theme_few() + 
  ylab("log10 CFU/ml")+ scale_x_continuous(breaks = 0:15)

#5 day control plots

controls = read.csv(file = "CFU-data/5daycontrols.csv")
summary_data_control <- controls %>%
  group_by(Media, Day) %>%
  summarise(mean_value = mean(log),
            sd_value = sd(log),
            count = n())
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Media'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
ggplot(data = summary_data_control, aes(x = Day, y = mean_value)) +geom_line(aes(color=Media), size = 1.2) +geom_point(data = controls, aes(x = Day, y = log, color=Media)) +
  geom_errorbar(data = summary_data_control, aes(x = Day, ymin = mean_value - sd_value, ymax = mean_value + sd_value), width=0.5) +
  ylim(0, 10)  +  
  theme(legend.position = "right") +
  theme_few()+ ylab("log10 CFU/ml")+ scale_x_continuous(breaks = 0:5)+scale_color_manual(values=custom_palette)

#Population level Phenotype studies

Conditioning_confirmation = read.csv(file = "Conditioning validation/CFU_experiment_02042024.csv")
summary_data_condition_confirmation <- Conditioning_confirmation %>%
  group_by(Media, Strain) %>%
  summarise(mean_value = mean(log),
            sd_value = sd(log),
            count = n())
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Media'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
Conditioning_confirmation$Media <- factor(Conditioning_confirmation$Media, levels = c("Mipro", "LowCF", "MedCF"))
Conditioning_confirmation_stats <- compare_means(log ~ Media, group.by = "Strain", data = Conditioning_confirmation, method = "t.test")

population_comp_plot=ggplot(data=Conditioning_confirmation) +geom_bar(stat="summary", position=position_dodge(1),aes(x=Media, y=log, fill=Media))+ geom_point(aes(x=Media, y=log, fill=Media))+ geom_errorbar(data=summary_data_condition_confirmation, aes(x=Media, ymin=mean_value-sd_value,ymax = mean_value + sd_value),width= 0.5)+facet_wrap(~Strain)+scale_fill_manual(values = custom_palette[c("LowCF", "MedCF", "Mipro")])+theme_few()+labs(y="log10 CFU/ml") 

png(filename="Figure1b.png", width = 7, height = 5, res = 300, units = "in")
population_comp_plot

#Strain Difference Volcano

Strain_volcano =read.csv("straindeifference_volcano.csv")

Strain_volcano_plot=ggplot(Strain_volcano, aes(x = Mean, y = -log10(p.adj))) +
  geom_point(color= "#7bccc4", aes(size= Mean), show.legend = F) +
  geom_text_repel(aes(label = Strain), vjust = -0.5, hjust = 0.5, size = 3)+theme_few()+labs(x="Δ log10CFU")
